commit 5f4af248345ee76c77080f97f5c737614f99d43a
Author: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Commit: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>

    K2.A.2 stateful path: transpose evicted-K/V before RoPE (fix quadratic broadcast)
    
    Surfaces the bug the user hit on Mac mini 2026-06-09 v3:
    
        RuntimeError: Invalid buffer size: 19.20 GiB
    
    at DLMRestoredVerifier._stateful_incremental_forward line ~1124
    in apply_rotary_pos_emb. The crash is NOT a real OOM — it's a
    silent quadratic broadcast caused by feeding apply_rotary_pos_emb
    a tensor in the wrong layout.
    
    Root cause:
    
      KVCapture's natural tensor layout (per kv_capture.py line 478,
      module docstring lines 102-103) is:
    
          [B, T, num_kv_heads, head_dim]
    
      This is the natural shape after the standard
      k_proj(hidden_states).view(B, T, kv_heads, head_dim) — T comes
      before kv_heads.
    
      HF's apply_rotary_pos_emb (and the entire HF attention pipeline
      downstream) expects the transposed layout:
    
          [B, num_heads, T, head_dim]
    
      The K1.D / K2.A.1 stateless path handles this correctly via
      prepare_restored_attention_kv (restored_attention.py line ~370;
      see its docstring lines 257-259 which explicitly document the
      layout difference and the internal transpose).
    
      The K2.A.2 stateful path at _stateful_incremental_forward
      re-implemented the evicted-K/V pre-compute pipeline WITHOUT
      going through prepare_restored_attention_kv, and forgot the
      transpose. Source comment at line 1119 even claimed
      '# [B, kv, n_ev, head_dim]' — a misleading lie about the
      actual KVCapture layout.
    
      Without the transpose, q.shape = [1, n_ev, num_kv_heads, head_dim]
      multiplied by cos.unsqueeze(unsqueeze_dim=1).shape =
      [1, 1, n_ev, head_dim]. Broadcasting pairs from right:
    
          head_dim vs head_dim   match
          kv_heads vs n_ev       broadcast (kv=1 → n_ev) — silent quadratic
          n_ev vs 1              broadcast (1 → n_ev)
          1 vs 1                 match
    
      Result: [B, n_ev, n_ev, head_dim]. At Gemma 3-1B's num_kv_heads=1
      + ctx280 (n_ev≈6345), this is 1 × 6345 × 6345 × 256 × 2 bytes
      bf16 ≈ 20.6 GB — crashes MPS with 'Invalid buffer size: 19.20
      GiB' (MPS rounds the request).
    
    Why synthetic CI tests didn't catch it:
    
      The existing _FakeAttention uses num_kv_heads=2. With kv_heads=2,
      the misshapen broadcast pairs
    
          kv_heads (2) vs n_ev (6345)
    
      which can NOT silently broadcast (neither is 1) — it raises a
      clean shape-mismatch RuntimeError instead of the quadratic
      materialisation. Only num_kv_heads=1 (Gemma 3-1B's GQA-collapsed
      config) reproduces the silent quadratic path.
    
      The K2.A.2 implementation tests in
      test_dlm_restored_verifier_stateful.py all use the default
      num_kv_heads=2 and therefore could not detect this bug.
    
      This is a recurring lesson: synthetic test fixtures must mirror
      the EDGE CASE shape configurations of the real model (here,
      the GQA-collapsed num_kv_heads=1) — using only 'safe' middle-
      ground shapes hides interaction bugs that only manifest at
      the production shape.
    
    Fix:
    
      At inference_engine/v04/dlm_restored_verifier.py line 1118-1136,
      add explicit .transpose(1, 2).contiguous() on K_pre and V_pre
      BEFORE the k_norm + apply_rotary_pos_emb call:
    
          K_pre = evicted_capture.keys[layer_idx].transpose(1, 2).contiguous()
          V_pre = evicted_capture.values[layer_idx].transpose(1, 2).contiguous()
    
      Mirrors what prepare_restored_attention_kv does internally.
      Layout after fix: [B, num_kv_heads, n_evicted, head_dim] —
      matches HF attention pipeline contract that V04SessionCache
      expects (see _V04SessionCache.update line 282 type comment).
    
    Regression tests:
    
      tests/inference_engine/v04/test_dlm_restored_verifier_stateful.py
      adds TestStatefulIncrementalEvictedKVShape with two tests:
    
      1. test_stateful_incremental_does_not_quadratic_broadcast
         End-to-end: bootstrap forward + incremental forward through
         a num_kv_heads=1 _FakeModel, with a strict
         apply_rotary_pos_emb stub that asserts q is in the
         [B, num_heads, T, head_dim] layout. Pre-fix the assertion
         fires with 'q layout bug: q has shape [1, 5, 1, 4] but cos
         has T=5'. Post-fix the test passes.
    
      2. test_evicted_kv_handed_to_cache_in_attention_layout
         Patches V04SessionCache to capture set_evicted_kv arguments,
         drives _stateful_incremental_forward, asserts the K_evicted /
         V_evicted shapes handed to the cache are
         (B=1, num_kv_heads=1, n_evicted=5, head_dim=4) — the standard
         HF attention layout. Pre-fix shapes are
         (B=1, n_evicted=5, num_kv_heads=1, head_dim=4) and the
         assertion fails clearly.
    
      Both tests use the new _gemma3_1b_shape_model helper that
      overrides _FakeModel.config to set num_key_value_heads=1
      (mirrors Gemma 3-1B's GQA-collapsed production config — the
      configuration where the bug actually manifests).
    
      Verified by stashing the fix and re-running:
        pre-fix:  2 failed (assertion fires with the exact error
                  shape the user reported)
        post-fix: 2 passed (281 total + 2 new = 283 passing)
    
    Scope concern:
    
      This fix is in v0.4 K2.A.2 code (PR #90), not in this PR's
      natural surface area (the Mac reviewer scripts). Same scope-
      concern as the dtype hotfix in this PR's previous commit:
      the proper home is a hotfix PR off the K2.A.2 codebase, but
      the user is actively waiting on production-shape evidence and
      the bug blocks ANY Gemma 3-1B class (num_kv_heads=1) stateful
      KL ON path on any device.
    
      Carrying both K2.A fixes (dtype hotfix + this transpose hotfix)
      on the Mac reviewer branch is the unblock path. A clean backport
      PR will follow once the v04 stack settles, so both fixes land
      in their proper code-history homes:
    
        * dtype hotfix → backport into PR #84 (K2.A.1) lineage
        * transpose hotfix → backport into PR #90 (K2.A.2) lineage
    
    Lessons codified:
    
      * KVCapture's [B, T, kv, head_dim] layout vs HF attention's
        [B, kv, T, head_dim] layout is a known footgun. Anywhere a
        KVCapture tensor enters the HF attention pipeline (k_norm,
        apply_rotary_pos_emb, attention forward), it MUST be
        transposed first. There are now exactly two call sites:
        prepare_restored_attention_kv (handles it) and
        _stateful_incremental_forward (handled by this PR).
    
      * Synthetic test fixtures must include the production GQA shape
        (num_kv_heads=1 for Gemma 3-1B class). The _FakeConfig default
        num_key_value_heads=2 was chosen for 'safety' (avoids tying
        tests to one specific real model) but that 'safety' is the
        very property that hid this bug. Future K-stage tests should
        parameterise num_kv_heads ∈ {1, 2, 4} to cover the GQA
        configurations actually used in production.
    
      * The misleading source comment at line 1119 ('# [B, kv, n_ev,
        head_dim]') was written by the K2.A.2 author from intent
        rather than from inspection. After this PR the comment is
        corrected to reflect the actual KVCapture shape and the
        transpose is documented inline.
    
