commit 736584bdd7d0bb0e5a7c3ab8196e25b9ac89916e
Author: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Commit: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>

    K3 Stage 2: fix draft query layout per copy_and_expand_dflash_inputs_kernel
    
    The kernel revealed two draft-extraction bugs:
      * bonus query sits at position C (= last_pos+1), not C-1; masks at C+1..
      * the SAMPLED (drafted) tokens are the MASK positions (query_off>0), NOT
        the bonus; and the bonus is the verifier's greedy next token t_C
        (guaranteed-correct first token), not committed[-1].
    
    draft_block now: query=[t_C, mask*L] at positions [C, C+1..C+L]; drafts =
    argmax over mask positions (logits[1:1+L]) for positions C+1..C+L.
    AuxHiddenProvider.aux_hidden_context returns (aux_list, bonus_token_id);
    harness builds candidate=[bonus]+drafts and counts draft acceptance
    (excluding the always-correct bonus). 20 tests pass.
    
    Co-authored-by: FluffyAIcode <FluffyAIcode@users.noreply.github.com>

