        real ckpt [1,6,11,17,22,27] -> aux [2,7,12,18,23,28].
      * DFlashDrafter — self-contained Qwen3 backbone (5 layers: GQA + q/k RMSNorm
        + RoPE + SwiGLU) + fc (num_aux*hidden -> hidden) + hidden_norm + norm,
        matching the checkpoint weight names 1:1 (load_state_dict_from_hf /
        from_pretrained over model.safetensors). Owns no embed/lm_head — shares
        the verifier's (Gemma sqrt(hidden) scaling + final_logit_softcapping).
      * draft_block — block-diffusion denoise: non-causal block attention
        (PR #41703), aux-conditioned register token, low-confidence remasking.
      * DFlashProposer — propose_block(committed, L, steps) -> BlockProposal,
        drop-in for SpeculativeDecoder; pulls verifier aux hidden via an
        injectable AuxHiddenProvider + shared embed/lm_head.
    
    Tests (tests/inference_engine/v04/test_dflash_drafter.py, 20 cases, synthetic
    config — no 52GB download): config parsing + aux-shift, projection shapes,
    HF weight-name layout, non-mask draft output, num_steps clamp, determinism,
    and the propose_block contract. 273 v04 tests pass.
    
    Fidelity status: backbone/weights/aux-selection/non-causal-mask are faithful
    and unit-tested; the EAGLE-3<->block fusion + denoise schedule are a
    documented principled impl. Reproducing the reference acceptance profile is
    Stage 2 (H200, real weights) and may need reconciliation vs qwen3_dflash.py.
    
    Per the K3 design contract, spec-decode integration is its own PR; this is
    the drafter+proposer foundation.
    
