    K2.A.2: stateful caching implementation — verifier per-step O(1) in T
    
    User directive: open K2.A.2 实施 PR.
    
    K2.A.2 formal commitment per ADR §11.11.12 (PR #84 promoted from
    "future PR" to binding architectural commitment):
    
    * Stateful compressed K/V cache surviving across forwards
    * Verifier per-step forward becomes O(1) in T (not O(T))
    * Per-step peak drops from ~2× to ~1× O(T × hidden_dim)
    * §11.13 invariant: peak_allocated_bytes(K2.A.2) < peak(K1.D) − weights_size at the same T
    * Closes §11.8 throughput gate (c) and §11.11.9 sustained-memory empirical gap
    
    K2.A.1 empirical baseline from PR #88 §11.11.13.6:
    * Throughput: ≥ 1.21 tok/s at 21k (1.3× of K2.A.1 KL ON 0.93)
    * Recall: within 1pp of 0.600 at 21k
    * Per-step peak: must drop measurably from 30 GB at 21k
    
    This PR delivers the implementation; empirical evidence collection
    on real Gemma 3-1B (vast + Mac M4) is a follow-up.
    
    Three new architectural primitives:
    
    1. _SessionState dataclass (inference_engine/v04/dlm_restored_verifier.py)
       * cache_token_count: int (how many tokens already processed in session)
       * compressors: Optional[List[KVCompressor]] (persisted across forwards
         when stateful=True; None before first forward)
       * fresh() factory + dataclass field defaults
    
    2. _V04SessionCache class — implements HF Cache.update() contract for
       K2.A.2 stateful incremental decode.
       * Pre-computed evicted K/V per-layer (post-norm post-RoPE) set via
         set_evicted_kv(layer_idx, K_evicted, V_evicted) before model.forward
       * update(K_new, V_new, layer_idx, cache_kwargs) returns assembled
         full-T K, V tensor by combining:
           - decompressed cached K/V at resident positions
           - pre-computed proposer-restored K/V at evicted positions
           - new K/V at new positions (just from k_proj/k_norm/RoPE on new
             tokens)
       * Side effects: stores new K, V at new resident-eligible positions
         in compressor; evicts positions that age out of sliding window
    
    3. DLMRestoredVerifier extensions:
       * New stateful: bool = False constructor parameter (default preserves
         K1.D / K2.A.1 backward-compat)
       * New properties: stateful, cache_token_count
       * New reset_cache() method (no-op in stateless mode for symmetry)
       * forward() branches on stateful + cache_token_count > 0:
           - 0 → bootstrap path (K1.D-style full forward, persists compressors)
           - >0 → _stateful_incremental_forward path
       * _stateful_incremental_forward:
           - Validates input_ids extends prefix
           - Captures proposer K/V over full prefix (still O(T) per §11.3)
           - Pre-computes evicted K/V per layer (k_norm + RoPE applied to
             proposer's captured pre-norm pre-RoPE K/V)
           - Builds _V04SessionCache with persistent compressors
           - Runs model.forward(input_ids=new_tokens, position_ids=range(T_start,
             T_full), past_key_values=cache, use_cache=True)
           - Updates session state, returns full-T logits (zero-filled for
             pre-cache prefix; callers use only logits[:, -1, :] in greedy
             decode)
       * _restoration_active bootstrap branch persists compressors into
         _session_state.compressors so subsequent forwards reuse them
       * _get_full_position_embeddings: cos/sin at evicted positions; auto-
         discovers HF model.model.rotary_emb or accepts caller-injected
         rotary_emb_fn (test stubs, non-HF models)
    
    Tests (tests/inference_engine/v04/test_dlm_restored_verifier_stateful.py,
    27 new):
      TestStatefulFalseIsBackwardCompatible (4):
        * default constructor is stateless
        * stateful property reflects construction argument
        * stateless cache_token_count is zero (always)
    
      TestResetCacheBehaviour (3):
        * resets cache_token_count
        * clears compressors
        * no-op in stateless mode
    
      TestStatefulBootstrapForward (5):
        * returns logits shape matching stateless
        * persists compressors after first forward
        * advances cache_token_count
        * uses kv_compressor_factory once per layer
        * second bootstrap on same session reuses compressors
    
      TestStatefulIncrementalForward (2):
        * processes only new tokens (cache_token_count → T_full)
        * returns full-T logits shape
    
      TestStatefulInputValidation (3):
        * shrinking prefix raises ValueError
        * same-length prefix raises ValueError
        * reset_cache after shrinking unblocks new session
    
      TestSessionStateDataclass (3):
        * fresh() factory
        * default constructor
        * custom initialization
    
      TestV04SessionCache (7):
        * get_seq_length
        * set_partition
        * set_evicted_kv
        * update returns full K/V at T_full
        * update with evicted uses set_evicted_kv values correctly
        * update without set_evicted_kv raises (when evicted positions present)
        * update with mismatched n_new raises
    
    K1.E NIAH runner integration (scripts/research/k1e_niah_validation.py):
      * New --stateful flag enabling K2.A.2 mode
